class Solution {
    public boolean canJump(int[] nums) {
        int farthest = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length && i <= farthest; i++){
            if (nums[i] + i > farthest){
                farthest = nums[i] + i;
            }
            if (farthest >= nums.length - 1){
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
}

/
Note:

(Greedy Algorithms: Greedy is an algorithmic paradigm that builds up a solution piece by piece, 
always choosing the next piece that offers the most obvious and immediate benefit. 
So the problems where choosing locally optimal also leads to global solution are best fit for Greedy.)

Greedy Algorithms: Computing the Farthest index away from index[0].
Farthest index = x + nums[x]

